title: For Sale:  Finnish M28-76 with scope mount and scope
postcontent:
This is a Finnish M28-76 target rifle. There were 990 of these imported. Of those an estimated "Couple Hundred" had scope bases attached. There is less information regarding the actual scope mounts but I have heard "less than 50" and "50 to 75". Surfice it to say it wasn't a lot. But the prize is the scope itself. They were not imported or available to the best of my knowledge. I looked long and hard to locate a Finnish original scope for the M28-76 however that proved more difficult than I imagined. The scope on this rifle IS the correct scope but of a different name. The original German manufacturer of the Finnish scope is the same manufacturer of this scope. It is identical in every way except the printed name. It is not a copy, fake or reproduction. It is the genuine item, just not from Finland. This was very difficult to locate. In this configuration it is very unique and you may not find another one, original or otherwise. The correct Original scope case is included as shown in the pictures. You will note the scope has an elevation adjustment but not a windage. That's because the scope mount has the windage adjustment built in.This rifle also comes with the original Diopter sight and mounting screw.
The Bipod is aftermarket and the palm stop/bipod mount is also. They attach to the rail and remove quickly if not desired. It also has a quick release sling mount. I have an ORIGINAL Sling and ORIGINAL sling mount that comes with this rifle. (Not Pictured). This rifle has not shot surplus ammunition. This rifle shoots 7.62x53r Finnish ammunition. I hand load myself for this rifle.
The stock on this firearm is original however the rubber pad was not there when I purchased it. There was reminants of glue and it was rather worn and ragged on the butt. Even though that was "original" it was rough at best. I sanded the glue off and coated the stock in tung oil. It looks nice but not shiny or thick. It has a dull look and the grain of the wood shows nicely. Basically, it looks beautiful.Many more high resolution pictures available upon request.
